  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Determine the efficiency of a myéloablative conditioning associating Fludarabine,
      Thymoglobuline, and intravenous Busulfan with adapted dose, according to a pharmacokinetics
      realized in the first day of administration (or J-6 of the conditioning) of the busulfan, in
      preparation for a allogenic transplant family or not family compatible HLA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
